               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols. 3ra-75va)
                     II) Maṣḥafa lǝdätu la-ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot “Book of the Genealogy of Takla
                     Haymanot” (fols. 75va-76vb)
 - Genealogy of Takla Hāymānot (fols.
                     75va-76vb)
 
 Additiones 1-2; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="3ra" to="76vb"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1008DossierTH">Hagiographic Dossier of Takla Hāymānot</title>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="75va"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4114GadlaT">The Acts of Takla Hāymānot</title>
                        <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                        <note>The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the
                           Dabra Libānos recension of the Gadla Takla Hāymānot (close, but not
                           identical to the <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/8SCM474J"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1906Taklahaymanot"/><title level="m">The Life of Takla Hâymânôt, in the version of Dabra Lîbanôs, and The miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the version of Dabra Lîbanôs</title><author><forename>E. A. Wallis</forename><surname>Budge</surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Privately printed for Lady Meux</publisher><date>1906</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Budge1906Taklahaymanot</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Budge1906Taklahaymanot</note></bibl>). </note>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1.1">
                           <locus from="75va" to="76vb"/>
                           <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3972Mashaf">Maṣḥafa lǝdatu la-ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot</title>
                           <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                           <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1.1.1">
                              <locus from="75va" to="76vb"/>
                              <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3143Ledata">Genealogy of ʾabuna
                                 Takla Haymanot</title>
                              <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                              
                           </msItem>
                           
                           <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1.1.2">
                              <locus from="76rb" to="76vb"/>
                              <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6591MonGenealogy">Zenā manakosāt "History of the Monks"</title>
                           </msItem>
                           
                           
                        </msItem>
                        
                     </msItem>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#76vb">76vb</locus>ተፈጸመ፡ ገድሉ፡ ለብፁዕ፡ ወለቅዱስ፡ ብእሴ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አቡነ፡
                        ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ጸሐየ፡ ዓለም፡ ሰባኬ፡ ግብር፡ ሐዲስ፡ ኮከበ፡ ገዳም፡ በጽጌ፡ አዕምሮ፡ ቅሱም። ረድኤተ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አብ፡
                        ይዕቀቦ፡ ለገብሩ፡ ተክለ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወለጸሐፊሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ዋህድ፡ ምስለ፡ አቡሁ፡ ወእሙ፡ ምስለ፡ አንባቢሁ፡ ወተርጓሚሁ፡
                        ወምስሌነ፡ አሜን፡ ይኩን፡<foreign xml:lang="en">The Vita of the blessed
                        and saint man of God, our father Takla Hāymānot, the sun of the world, the
                        preacher of the new deed, the star of the desert, who has tasted from the
                        flower of wisdom, is completed. May the help of this father protect his servant
                        Takla Giyorgis, and the scribe <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12937GabraWahedScribe">Gabra Wahǝd</persName>, together with his father and his
                        mother, with its reader and its interpreter, and with us (all). Amen. So be it.</foreign>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
   
                  
                  
